profile:
SAUZTEQ ENGINEERING offers structural engineering design services. 
We are open for business and we are following Ontario, Canadian and WHO advice & restrictions for Covid-19.

The company is licensed by the Professional Engineers of Ontario and fully insured. 
We provide structural engineering services for design of new and renovation of the existing buildings. 
With more than 20 years’ experience, our services cover residential, industrial and commercial developments. 

Design services include steel, reinforced concrete, wood and masonry structures. 
Other services include site inspection, consultation, providing report during the construction and helping clients to get the permit. 

We work for contractors, homeowners, architects, realtors and property managers. 
We provide practical and optimized cost solutions to meet our client’s needs. 
We aim to make our designs as clear and easy to understand as possible.

profile:
A design/build renovation company that specialized in large scale renovations. You can be sure that your home IS in good hands with Team Shane. We walk along side you through the concept, design, and build stages of your dream home. With our in-house design team, capable of all things from 3 dimensional renderings to complete permit drawings, we can help you turn your vision into a plan that can be built.

We understand that renovating is about much more than the actual build. We know that establishing a relationship, developing trust, and clear communication are the ONLY ways to give you the renovation you deserve.

Preliminary Package
We start with a design consultation on site to discuss ideas and plans for your project. We can provide the knowledge and expertise to assist you in visualizing your ideas and formulating a budget.

Architectural Design
We can provide you with the necessary construction drawings to ensure things get built properly and obtain any necessary permits.

Turning your dream into a reality begins with understanding what the end result may look like. We can help you with this by providing both concept plans and 3-Dimensional visuals.

Project Management
Whether your project is a whole home renovation, addition, or brand new construction, we can provide full general contracting services from start to finish.


Completing your project is not the end of our relationship. We provide for a full 5 year warranty on all work we do and will be there should any service issues arise

profile: Property Pathways is an Architectural Design that specialize in building additions, basement apartment creation. We work extensively with municipalities thoughout the GTA and surrounding area where we submit approximately 100- 120 permit application annually. Our client building permit needs are meet with our end to end service starting with an initial virtual consultation where we discuss the renovation goals, planning challenges, design solutions and schedule site visit. On our site visit we capture all site conditions with a 3D laser scanner. Once the site data is processed and the existing 3D model developed, we conduct a virtual 3D walkthrough design discussion of the design for client comments and approval. The next steps is permit production which involves BIM and Engineer team. Then the permit drawing set is turned over to our Permit Expeditor to ensure the most efficient permit review and approval regardless of the municipality. This is our "done for you" process that delivers the result every time. In the event there is a minor variance, conservation authority, or site plan control application required to advance the construction permit, our team is well equipped and experience working through these processes.

profile:
Kingswood Engineers specializes in value-added residential architectural design and engineering projects, including: home additions, additional storey expansions, foundation/floor system/roof truss designs, new build construction plans, home renovation/remodeling plans, HVAC drawings and analysis for removal of load bearing walls or beam selection.  We have considerable experience working with municipalities to provide building permits for new build construction and renovations/remodeling as well as designing permitted legal accessory unit dwellings (e.g. "income suites").  

Our team has the capability and experience to deliver the planning and engineering analysis for your residential project.

Are you are a homeowner remodeling your home? Or a contractor who requires an engineer's analysis? We are licensed engineers and architectural designers who can provide stamped drawings, floor layouts and building permit plans for your project that let you build with confidence.

We provide both the engineering and architectural know-how open and transform your space into something exceptional.

We specialize in all the structural analysis, architectural layouts and drawings, and engineering approval stamp you need for your home renovation project.

Our team provides professional design advice for home additions, renovations, extensions, decks, garages, retaining walls, legal accessory dwellings and new home construction. We can also complete zoning reviews that help you plan your build and provide analysis for load bearing wall removal. Furthermore, our team can design foundations, roof trusses, floor systems and HVAC systems.

We can provide the analysis and drawings for your next project or renovation - give us a call today!

Call: 289-206-7556
